enge "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"How do we use vehicles to help people?"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Spatial Sense "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Children develop a sense of spatial relationships early on and they use perceptual information to guide their own motions and interactions. Encourage children to describe the position of classmates or items using location words and phrases so that they can start to describe how they interact with their environment."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_2","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"OUR COMMUNITY "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 4: Vehicles at Work"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_2","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Share the Mind Builder: Classify and Organize "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Point out to children that items like vehicles can be sorted by things about them that you can see, like color or size, and also by things they do, like move things or help people. Practice sorting by having children sort themselves according to something you can see, like shirt color. Provide support as needed. Re-sort by a different attribute, such as wearing short/long sleeves. "},{"typ