lement","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Classification:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" As you read, point out similarities and differences between the vehicles in each category. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 2–3  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"This section is about vehicles we ride in. These are the cars and trucks we take to get places, and that bring goods to us. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 4–7 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We can sort vehicles by size, or how big they are. Is a bus bigger or smaller than a car? We can also sort them by what they do. How are a car and a bus like each other? How are they different? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"sort"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 20–27 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"We can also sort vehicles by the sounds they make. Which vehicles have sirens? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 32–33 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What do tractors do? How is it different from a car? "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"tractor"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages. 34–35 "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"What does the garbage truck do? Is it like what a tractor does? Would you sort them into the same group as cars and buses? Why or why not? "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text_routine_bold","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"(MB)"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Extended Play "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask children to think of a vehicle from the book that they want to pretend to be. Have each child share which vehicle they want to pretend to be, and turn to that page in the book for them to review.  "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Once children have chosen their vehicles, have them pretend to be those vehicles by sounding like them or doing the work that the vehicle does. As a class, sort the vehicles represented by each child into different categories. You can sort by colors, sizes, sounds, or other attributes that children think of.  "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Shared Writing "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Transcribe children’s speech as they describe different types of vehicles and the categories they belong in."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"child-development-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_hed-green","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Child Development: Mind Builder "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_body","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"When classifying, children may instinctively recognize the similarities or differences between items without being able to verbalize them. Help children understand the idea of sorting by attribute, or category, by sorting and re-sorting a small set of items. First sort by one attribute, like color, size, or shape, and then re-sort the same set by a different attribute."}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"day_3","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"week","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_top-left_header_all-caps","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"OUR COMMUNITY "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_header_separator","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"|"}]},{"type":"text","text":"  WEEK 4: Vehicles at Work"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"circle-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Build Math Background "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Explain to children that when you count, each number represents a quantity one larger. Demonstrate by adding Connecting Cubes one at a time and checking the total."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Count of Ten "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Review the numbers one to ten with children. Practice counting out loud from one to ten while doing an action like standing on one foot. Encourage children to count along."}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule_day_3","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Focus on Vocabulary "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Introduce new vocabulary. "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_child_development_icon"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use 2.4.3 Vocabulary Card. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_vocab_words","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"bulldozer"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"story-time-section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section-block","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_no_paragraph_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit the Book "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Show the book cover. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Today we are going to reread "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_emphasis_non-ital","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Me and My Cars "}]},{"type":"text","text":"by Liesbet Slegers. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Lala Stick Puppet. "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Lala loves reading books with things she can count! "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements":[{"type":"element","name":"rac_column_heds_with_rule","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask the Guiding Question "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Different vehicles are used for different reasons. As we read today, I want you to think about this question: How do the vehicles in the book help us? "}]}]},{"type":"element","name":"section","elements